template:
Your task is to prepare a list of main sections of a book about {main_subject}.
Returned sections should cover {main_subject} very broadly including all important aspects.
Someone who would read this book shouldn't have to use any external source to become an expert in {main_subject}.
Here is a list of concepts which can be helpful to plan a structure of the book: {concepts}
Sections should be organized in a way that each section covers a different aspect of the subject without overlapping.
{instructs}
Each section should have a title, subtitle, description and a list of concepts to be covered in this section.
Concepts are tags which shoould be covered by following subsections. It is very important to distribute concepts between chapters so they won't overlap.
Return only a list of dictionaries, where each dictionary represents a section in json format.

example_output: 
    [
        {{
            "title": "Part I AI",
            "subtitle": "Basics of Artificial Intelligence",
            "description": "This section covers the fundamental concepts of AI.",
            "concepts": ["Machine Learning", "Neural Networks", "Deep Learning",...]
        }},
        {{
            "title": "Part II AI methods",
            "subtitle": "In-depth AI Methods",
            "description": "This section delves into advanced AI techniques.",
            "concepts": ["Reinforcement Learning", "Generative Adversarial Networks", "Natural Language Processing",...]
        }}
    ]
